.<img width="683" height="400" class="wp-image-1799319" style="width: 800px;" src="https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/Peter-Obi22.jpg" alt="2023: Peter Obi's presidency threatened as LP faction picks Ezenwafor as presidential candidate" srcset="https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/Peter-Obi22.jpg?width=683&amp;auto_optimize=medium 683w, https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/Peter-Obi22-300x176.jpg?width=300&amp;auto_optimize=medium 300w" sizes="(max-width: 683px) 100vw, 683px" /> By Ibrahim Hassan-Wuyo  Presidential candidate of the New Nigeria Peoples Party ( NNPP), Senator Rabiu Musa Kwankwaso has said that he is discussing with his counterpart in the Labour Party,Peter Obi on the possibility  of contesting for he presidency on the same ticket in 2023. He spoke in an interview with the BBC Hausa monitored by Vanguard on  Saturday.  According to.him, ” yes we are discussing with Peter Obi,or I will rather say a committee is working to see all that is necessary on teaming up with him, and our friends and relations have been coming to talk to us over the issue.” The former Governor of Kano state explained that their teaming up is important,looking at the fact that the APC and PDP did not picked their Vice Presidential candidates from.the Igbo tribe.